# React Hook Form Best Practices

Standards for using React Hook Form. Auto-included for TSX and JSX files.

<rule>
name: react_hook_form_best_practices
description: Best practices for using React Hook Form. Auto-included for TSX and JSX files.
globs: ["**/*.{tsx,jsx}"]
filters:
  - type: file_extension
    pattern: "\\.(tsx|jsx)$"
actions:
  - type: suggest
    message: |
      Follow these React Hook Form best practices:

      1. Form Setup:
         - Use proper form initialization
         - Implement proper validation schema
         - Use proper default values
         - Handle form submission properly

      2. Field Registration:
         - Use register method properly
         - Implement proper field validation
         - Handle field errors properly
         - Use proper field naming

      3. Validation Integration:
         - Use Zod or Yup integration
         - Implement custom validation
         - Handle async validation
         - Use proper error messages

      4. Performance Optimization:
         - Use uncontrolled components
         - Implement proper form watching
         - Handle form state properly
         - Use proper re-render optimization

      5. Form State Management:
         - Handle form submission state
         - Implement proper error handling
         - Use proper form reset
         - Handle form dirty state

      6. Using Boilerplate Form Components (AlignUI wrappers):
         - All reusable form controls live in `components/form/` and internally use `Controller`
         - Always pass `control` and `name` props; use `label`, `required`, `description`, `placeholder` as needed
         - Import from `@/components/form` (barrel):
           ```typescript
           import {
             FormInput,
             FormSelect,
             FormPassword,
             FormTextarea,
             FormCheckbox,
             FormDateInput,
             FormRichTextEditor,
             FormFileUpload,
             FormImageUpload,
           } from "@/components/form";
           ```
         - Typical usage with `useForm`:
           ```tsx
           type Values = {
             name: string;
             email: string;
             password: string;
             agree: boolean;
             dob: Date | null;
             bio: string;
             role: string;
             avatarUrl: string;
             imageUrl: string;
             about: string;
           };

           const { control, handleSubmit } = useForm<Values>({
             defaultValues: {
               name: "",
               email: "",
               password: "",
               agree: false,
               dob: null,
               bio: "",
               role: "",
               avatarUrl: "",
               imageUrl: "",
               about: "",
             },
           });

           return (
             <form onSubmit={handleSubmit(console.log)}>
               <FormInput control={control} name="name" label="Name" required />
               <FormInput control={control} name="email" type="email" label="Email" />
               <FormPassword control={control} name="password" label="Password" />
               <FormSelect
                 control={control}
                 name="role"
                 label="Role"
                 options={[
                   { value: "admin", label: "Admin" },
                   { value: "user", label: "User" },
                 ]}
                 placeholder="Select a role"
               />
               <FormTextarea control={control} name="bio" label="Bio" rows={4} maxLength={280} />
               <FormCheckbox control={control} name="agree" label="I agree to the terms" />
               <FormDateInput control={control} name="dob" label="Date of birth" />
               <FormRichTextEditor control={control} name="about" label="About" />
               <FormFileUpload
                 control={control}
                 name="avatarUrl"
                 label="Avatar"
                 uploadPath="/api/upload"
                 acceptedTypes={["image/*"]}
               />
               <FormImageUpload
                 control={control}
                 name="imageUrl"
                 label="Hero Image"
                 uploadPath="/api/upload"
                 acceptedTypes={["image/jpeg", "image/png", "image/webp"]}
               />
               <button type="submit">Submit</button>
             </form>
           );
           ```
         - Notes:
           - `FormSelect` requires an `options` array with `{ value, label }`
           - `FormDateInput` expects `Date | null` values and formats via `date-fns`
           - `FormFileUpload` and `FormImageUpload` require `uploadPath`; optionally use `uploadPrefix`, `acceptedTypes`, `maxSize`, `onUploadSuccess`, `onRemoveSuccess`
           - All components surface field errors via `FormField` automatically

